          "email": "cgao@research.att.com",
          "username": "cgao"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-02-11 21:47:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@Pam, This is my implementation of initial thoughts. I create a new endpoint \"/nativedecision\" for native xacml purpose. We can reuse app/json or app/yaml without needing a new content-type. I create a new native decision request class which derives from decision request and that is used in the new endpoint. Basically, user just need to provide the values to the fields, \"action\"=\"evaluate\" and \"request\"=\"raw xacml request string\". It will be routed to the native application by the \"action\". The raw request string will be converted to a xacml request as well as the url encoded policy string to a xacml PolicyType. Please let me know your thoughts and most importantly if I am on the right track.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "88f9ea06643cacef23f461ad0baabec23168a8a0",
