        "timestamp": "2020-02-12 00:25:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> @Pam, This is my implementation of initial thoughts. I create a new endpoint \"/nativedecision\" for native xacml purpose. We can reuse app/json or app/yaml without needing a new content-type. I create a new native decision request class which derives from decision request and that is used in the new endpoint. Basically, user just need to provide the values to the fields, \"action\"=\"evaluate\" and \"request\"=\"raw xacml request string\". It will be routed to the native application by the \"action\". The raw request string will be converted to a xacml request as well as the url encoded policy string to a xacml PolicyType. Please let me know your thoughts and most importantly if I am on the right track.\n\nI think though that I would prefer the user to just be able to set the payload as XACML XML and/or Json according to the specs.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
